Things work fine on Mac.
However, on a real device, calling `setSurfaceVelocity` shows no effects.

- cocos2d-x version: 3.13.1
- devices test on: iPhone 6, iOS 10.2
- developing environments
   - Xcode version: 8.2.1

Steps to Reproduce:
````
auto contactListener = EventListenerPhysicsContact::create();
contactListener->onContactPreSolve  = 
[=](cocos2d::PhysicsContact &contact, cocos2d::PhysicsContactPreSolve &solve)
{
    solve.setSurfaceVelocity(Vec2(1000, 1000));
    return true;
};
Director::getInstance()->getEventDispatcher()
    ->addEventListenerWithSceneGraphPriority(contactListener, this);
````
